# Blazor Component Structure Guidelines

## Component Organization
- All pages should inherit from [BasePage.razor](mdc:HabitKitClone/Components/BasePage.razor) for automatic theme initialization
- Use `@inherits BasePage` directive in page components
- Keep component-specific CSS in `.razor.css` files

## CSS File Structure
- Component CSS files should only contain component-specific styles
- Use CSS variables from [theme.css](mdc:HabitKitClone/wwwroot/theme.css) for all colors
- Follow mobile-first responsive design approach
- Use semantic class names that describe purpose, not appearance

## Component CSS Best Practices
```css
/* ✅ Good - Uses theme variables */
.my-component {
    background-color: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    color: var(--text-primary);
}

/* ❌ Bad - Hardcoded values */
.my-component {
    background-color: #161b22;
    border: 1px solid #30363d;
    color: #c9d1d9;
}
```

## File Naming Convention
- Component files: `ComponentName.razor`
- Component CSS: `ComponentName.razor.css`
- Models: `ComponentName/Models/ModelName.cs`

## Responsive Design
- Always start with mobile styles (no media queries)
- Use `@media (min-width: 768px)` for tablet
- Use `@media (min-width: 1024px)` for desktop
- Test on multiple screen sizes